Executive Profile
Allen A. Spizzo  Chief Financial Officer and Vice President, Hercules IncorporatedAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships59--
Background

		Mr. Allen A. Spizzo is a Business and Management Consultant focused on the chemicals, materials, biotechnology and pharmaceutical industries, since November 2008. Mr. Spizzo also serves as an investment adviser and asset management trustee. Mr. Spizzo served as the Chief Financial Officer and Vice President at Hercules Incorporated since March 22, 2004 until 2008. Mr. Spizzo served as Vice President of Corporate Development and Corporate Affairs at Hercules Incorporated ... from July 2002 to March 22, 2004. He served as Vice President of Strategic Planning at Hercules Incorporated from 2000 to March 22, 2004. Mr. Spizzo joined Hercules in 1979. After rejoining Hercules in 1997, he served as Director of Corporate Development. His experience with Hercules spans 35 years and includes a broad range of responsibilities in sales and marketing, mergers and acquisitions and business management. Mr. Spizzo served as Group Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Hercules' divested Metton America Incorporated composite materials business from 1995 to 1997. He served as Vice President and General Manager of FiberVisions and Pinova since April 2002. Prior to that, he served as Vice President and General Manager of BetzDearborn since August 2000 and Vice President of Business Operations for BetzDearborn Division since May 2000. He has been a Director of Vectra Corporation since June 1, 2015. He has been a Director of Ferro Corporation since October 20, 2016. He received an MBA degree in Finance from the University of Akron and a B.S. in Chemical Engineering from North Carolina State University.Read Full Background




